<br>
For every player that wants alignment restricted grouping back in, for example, there's another player that joined FV after the May 8th patch and has a multi-alignment guild and would want that rule left out.<br>
<br>
Personally I think a compromise <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>might</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> work.  Something along the lines of... alignments go back in, as do the XP bonuses / penalties for groups of similar / dissimilar alignments; but the grouping restrictions stay gone (a paladin and a shadowknight can still group, they just suffer an XP penalty while doing so).<br>
<br>
We probably wouldn't be able to get anything <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>new</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> added, because that would require new code, which requires $$, which is something SOE doesn't like to spend much of <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
